.TH ENGLINT 1 "2026-02-08" "englint" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
englint \- linter for detecting non-English text in source files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B englint
.RI <command>
.RI [ args... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B englint
scans source files and reports non-English characters based on configurable include,
exclude, and allow rules.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B scan
Scan paths for non-English text.
.TP
.B init
Create a default .englint.yaml config file.
.TP
.B version
Show version.
.SH SCAN FLAGS
.TP
.B --config <path>
Config file path (default: .englint.yaml).
.TP
.B --exclude <glob>
Repeatable exclude glob.
.TP
.B --include <glob>
Repeatable include glob.
.TP
.B --json
Machine-readable JSON output.
.TP
.B --fix
Auto-fix placeholder mode.
.TP
.B --severity <error|warning>
Default severity level.
.TP
.B --no-color
Disable color output.
.TP
.B --verbose
Print all scanned and skipped files.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I .englint.yaml
Project configuration file.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success, no non-English text found.
.TP
.B 1
Error or non-English text detected.
.SH SEE ALSO
README.md
